voring the secure Dog Park at Civic Center Park and scenic river trails.\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"city-rich-description\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",\"0\",{\"className\":\"rich-description-paragraph\",\"children\":[\"Clinton Township, Michigan, offers a blend of suburban comfort and natural beauty, making it a great place for dog owners. The community hub is the \",[\"$\",\"$L12\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"https://clintontownship.com/Facilities/Facility/Details/Dog-Park-10\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"Clinton Township Dog Park\"}],null,\" located within Civic Center Park, which provides a secure, members-only space for off-leash socialization. For those who prefer on-leash adventures, the Clinton River Trail offers a picturesque route through the area's green spaces. Many residents visit our \",[\"$\",\"$L12\",\"4\",{\"href\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/about\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"about page\"}],null,\" to learn more about our focus on professional socialization hubs that align with the township's family-oriented values.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"1\",{\"className\":\"rich-description-paragraph\",\"children\":[\"Maintaining a safe and pleasant environment is a priority for the township, supported by strict leash laws in all public areas outside of the designated dog park. Dogs must be on a leash of six feet or less to ensure the safety of all park users. Local owners are proactive about pet wellness, often utilizing professional \",[\"$\",\"$L12\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/training-facilities\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"training facilities\"}],null,\" to maintain social etiquette. During the snowy Michigan winters, there is growing interest in \",[\"$\",\"$L12\",\"4\",{\"href\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/how-it-works\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"how it works\"}],null,\" for indoor play, providing a consistent, climate-controlled socialization alternative.\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-cta-row\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L2d\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-cta primary\",\"targetId\":\"park-directory\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-list-check\"}],\"Browse directory\"]}],[\"$\",\"$L2d\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-cta ghost\",\"targetId\":\"map-and-neighborhoods\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-geo-alt\"}],\"Open map\"]}],[\"$\",\"$L12\",null,{\"href\":\"/list-your-park\",\"className\":\"hero-cta text-link\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-plus-circle\"}],\"Submit a park\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-footnotes\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",\"Data refreshed weekly\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-sparkles\"}],\" \",\"Data refreshed weekly\"]}],[\"$\",\"span\",\"Live availability coming soon\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-sparkles\"}],\" \",\"Live availability coming soon\"]}]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"city-hero-visual\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-image-card\",\"children\":[\"$L2e\",\"$L2f\"]}]}]]}]}],\"$L30\",\"$L31\",\"$L32\",\"$L33\",\"$L34\",\"$L35\",\"$undefined\",\"$L36\",\"$L37\",false,\"$L38\",\"$L39\"]}]\n2a:[\"$\",\"footer\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-new\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-container\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-grid\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-column\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h4\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-heading\",\"children\":\"IndoorDogPark\"}],[\"$\",\"ul\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-links\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"li\",null,{\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L12\",null,{\"href\":\"/about\",\"children\":\"